# PHP в†’ Next.js Migration Plan
## Coaching Center Management System (Science Lab)

A complete migration from a PHP/MariaDB monolith to a modern **Next.js 14+ (App Router)** application backed by **PostgreSQL**.

---

## рџ“Њ Technology Decision: PostgreSQL over MongoDB

| Factor | PostgreSQL вњ… | MongoDB |
|---|---|---|
| Data structure | Relational вЂ” perfectly fits the existing normalized table design | Document model would require denormalizing relational data |
| Complex queries | Native JOINs (marks Г— exams Г— subjects Г— students) | Requires `$lookup` aggregations, more complex |
| Financial integrity | ACID transactions for fees/receipts | Less suited without 2-phase commits |
| Existing schema | Direct 1-to-1 migration of MySQL tables | Requires schema redesign |
| Reporting | Aggregate functions (`SUM`, `GROUP BY`) are native | Limited aggregation pipeline |

**Verdict в†’ PostgreSQL** is the clear winner for this application due to its relational data model and the nature of the academic/financial reporting queries.

---

