## рџ—„пёЏ Database Schema (PostgreSQL / Prisma)

### Current PHP Tables в†’ New Prisma Models

```
batchtbl     в†’ Batch
exptbl       в†’ Expense
feetbl       в†’ FeeRecord
imgtbl       в†’ GalleryImage
marktbl      в†’ Mark
rcpttbl      в†’ Receipt
schtbl       в†’ School
stdtbl       в†’ Student
sylltbl      в†’ Syllabus
tchclasstbl  в†’ TeacherClassLog
tchtbl       в†’ Teacher
usertbl      в†’ User
xmsubtbl     в†’ ExamSubject
xmtbl        в†’ Exam
```

### Key Schema Improvements over the PHP version

1. **`feetbl` redesign** вЂ” The current design uses 12 monthly columns (`Jan`, `Feb`, ..., `Dec1`). This will be normalized into rows in `receipts` instead, which is already present in `rcpttbl`. The `feetbl` with hard-coded months is an anti-pattern that will be eliminated.
2. **Password hashing** вЂ” Current passwords in `usertbl` are stored in **plaintext**. Migration will hash all passwords with **bcrypt**.
3. **Proper FKs and relationships** вЂ” The PHP schema lacks foreign key constraints. Prisma schema will enforce referential integrity.
4. **`batchid` type fix** вЂ” `stdtbl.batchid` is a `varchar` despite `batchtbl.batchid` being `int`. Prisma will enforce correct types.

### Prisma Schema (condensed)

```prisma
model User {
  id           Int       @id @default(autoincrement())
  username     String    @unique
  password     String    // bcrypt hashed
  role         Role      // ADMIN, STAFF, STUDENT, TEACHER
  active       Boolean   @default(true)
}

enum Role { ADMIN STAFF STUDENT TEACHER }

model Student {
  id         Int       @id @default(autoincrement())
  name       String
  fatherName String
  motherName String
  smsMobile  String
  homeMobile String?
  image      String?
  active     Boolean   @default(true)
  schoolId   Int
  batchId    Int
  address    String
  gender     String
  email      String?
  dob        DateTime?
  class      String    // Six, Seven, Eight, Nine, Ten
  school     School    @relation(fields: [schoolId], references: [id])
  batch      Batch     @relation(fields: [batchId], references: [id])
  marks      Mark[]
  receipts   Receipt[]
}

model Teacher {
  id        Int      @id @default(autoincrement())
  name      String
  mobile    String   @unique
  image     String?
  gender    String
  email     String
  perClass  Int      // payment per class
  due       Int      @default(0)
  classLogs TeacherClassLog[]
  examSubjects ExamSubject[]
}

model Batch {
  id        Int       @id @default(autoincrement())
  classId   String    // "Six", "Seven", etc.
  name      String    // "8A", "9B", etc.
  students  Student[]
}

model School {
  id       Int       @id @default(autoincrement())
  name     String
  students Student[]
}

model Exam {
  id       Int           @id @default(autoincrement())
  type     String        // "Monthly", "Annual"
  month    String        // "Jan", "Feb", etc.
  class    String
  subjects ExamSubject[]
}

model ExamSubject {
  id        Int      @id @default(autoincrement())
  examId    Int
  subject   String
  teacherId Int
  totalMark Int
  examDate  DateTime
  status    Int
  topics    String
  exam      Exam     @relation(fields: [examId], references: [id])
  teacher   Teacher  @relation(fields: [teacherId], references: [id])
  marks     Mark[]
}

model Mark {
  id           Int         @id @default(autoincrement())
  examSubjectId Int
  studentId    Int
  written      Float
  objective    Float
  examSubject  ExamSubject @relation(fields: [examSubjectId], references: [id])
  student      Student     @relation(fields: [studentId], references: [id])
}

model Receipt {
  id        Int      @id @default(autoincrement())
  studentId Int
  month     String
  amount    Int
  date      DateTime
  student   Student  @relation(fields: [studentId], references: [id])
}

model Expense {
  id          Int      @id @default(autoincrement())
  description String
  amount      Int
  date        DateTime
}

model Syllabus {
  id    Int    @id @default(autoincrement())
  image String
  class String
  month String
}

model GalleryImage {
  id          Int    @id @default(autoincrement())
  image       String
  heading     String
  description String
}

model TeacherClassLog {
  id        Int      @id @default(autoincrement())
  teacherId Int
  date      DateTime
  classes   Int
  month     String
  notebook  Int
  other     Int
  paid      Int
  perClass  Int
  teacher   Teacher  @relation(fields: [teacherId], references: [id])
}
```

