## рџљЂ Migration Phases

### Phase 1 вЂ” Setup & Foundation (Week 1вЂ“2)
- [ ] Initialize Next.js 14 project (TypeScript + App Router)
- [ ] Set up PostgreSQL (local Docker or cloud вЂ” Neon/Supabase)
- [ ] Write Prisma schema and generate migrations
- [ ] Set up NextAuth.js with credentials provider
- [ ] Create middleware for route protection
- [ ] Create base layouts for all 4 role areas
- [ ] Build shared UI components (sidebar, navbar, data tables)

### Phase 2 вЂ” Data Migration (Week 2вЂ“3)
- [ ] Write a Node.js migration script to read from MySQL dump and insert into PostgreSQL
- [ ] Hash all existing plaintext passwords with bcrypt during migration
- [ ] Validate data integrity (student count, exam count, mark count matches)
- [ ] Fix `batchid` type inconsistency during migration
- [ ] Normalize `feetbl` into `receipts` using `rcpttbl` as source of truth
- [ ] Test with a sample of 10 students end-to-end

### Phase 3 вЂ” Core Modules (Week 3вЂ“5)
- [ ] Student CRUD (list, add, edit, admit, profile photo upload)
- [ ] Teacher CRUD + class log
- [ ] Exam creation + subject management
- [ ] Mark input (bulk per exam subject) + mark edit
- [ ] Results view (aggregated marks per student per exam)
- [ ] Batch/class management

### Phase 4 вЂ” Finance Modules (Week 5вЂ“6)
- [ ] Fee/Receipt management (record payment, monthly status)
- [ ] Expense tracking
- [ ] Bill/receipt PDF print view (replacing PHP print page)
- [ ] Teacher billing (`tchclasstbl`)

### Phase 5 вЂ” Student & Teacher Portals (Week 6вЂ“7)
- [ ] Student portal: results, fees status, syllabus view
- [ ] Teacher portal: mark entry, edit, exam view, syllabus
- [ ] Staff portal: all modules except finance

### Phase 6 вЂ” Polish & Extras (Week 7вЂ“8)
- [ ] Gallery management with image upload
- [ ] Syllabus image upload
- [ ] SMS integration (optional)
- [ ] Dashboard charts/statistics (Chart.js or Recharts)
- [ ] Print/PDF receipts and result sheets
- [ ] Responsive mobile design
- [ ] Comprehensive testing

